======================================================================
PART 2: MAX α₂ AS FUNCTION OF dc3
======================================================================

  At n=6: There are C(6,3)/2 = 10 complementary triple-pairs.
  dp33 = #{pairs where BOTH triples are 3-cycles}
  So dp33 ≤ 10.
    dc3= 0: max(α₂) = 0
    dc3= 1: max(α₂) = 0
    dc3= 2: max(α₂) = 1
    dc3= 3: max(α₂) = 0
    dc3= 4: max(α₂) = 1
    dc3= 5: max(α₂) = 1
    dc3= 6: max(α₂) = 2
    dc3= 7: max(α₂) = 2
    dc3= 8: max(α₂) = 4

