======================================================================
PART 4: DISJOINTNESS GRAPH AT n=7
======================================================================
  Disjointness graph on C(7,3)=35 triples:
  Each vertex has degree 4 (choose 3 from 4 remaining vertices).
  Total edges: 35*4/2 = 70.
  α₂ = edges in induced subgraph on cyclic triples.
  trial 0: dc3=13, α₂=12, dp33=12, density=0.154
